a and Mexico to build his case. This book upends many common hypotheses and policy recommendations, providing the most comprehensive treatment of revenue and political stability to date"--cProvided by publisher.  a16 0aPolitical stabilityxEconomic aspects. 0aRepresentative government and representationxEconomic aspects. 0aDemocracyxEconomic aspects. 0aEconomic assistancexPolitical aspects. 0aFiscal policy. 0aTaxation. 0aRevenue. 0aCambridge studies in comparative politics.423Cover imageuhttp://assets.cambridge.org/97811070/76778/cover/9781107076778.jpg  aJC 330.2 M68 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035217411  aJC 330.2 M68 2015wLCc1i0162035217411lON_SHELFmUAAUGp$150.00rYsYtBOOKu1/9/201501ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n99047878bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/23931812